does not use any client-side state, such as cookies or localStorage, to collect usage metrics. Cloudflare Web Analytics also don’t “fingerprint” individuals via their IP address, User Agent string, or any other data for the purpose of displaying analytics.
Information you provide
If you contact us for customer support (via Report Bug or Contact), we may obtain and maintain any information you choose to provide, including your name, contact info such as your email address, as well as information about your devices such as its device type, OS type, and logs.
We will use this information to address and investigate the issues you have raised, to provide you support, and to improve our customer support service.
Bug reports are emailed to us through your email app. So, if you want,
you can delete unwanted information
from the compose screen of your email app.
The report may include, but is not limited to, the following information:
App information: version, configuration, execution environment, etc
System software information: OS name and version, WebView version, etc
Hardware information: manufacturer, model, CPU architecture, screen resolution, etc
Logs: app activity log, system log (logcat) of the app, etc
Crash logs: stack trace, the timestamp of when the crash occurred, etc
Diagnostics data: app running time, memory usage, etc
App permissions
android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE
This permissions is required to read files on devices running
Android 12L and lower
.
The files are used for local processing and WE DO NOT COLLECT them for any other purposes.
android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE
This permission is required to write files on devices running
Android 10 and lower
.
The files are used to store the processing results and WE DO NOT COLLECT them for any other purposes.
android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES
This permission is required to read and write images on devices running
Android 13 and higher
.
Images are used for local processing and WE DO NOT COLLECT them for any other purposes.
Since the core function of Photo Editor is to edit photos on the device, Photo Editor needs the READ_MEDIA_IMAGES permission for broad access to photos. We have submitted a declaration and received approval for use under
Details on Google Play's Photo and Video Permissions policy
.
android.permission.ACCESS_MEDIA_LOCATION
This permission is required to preserve GPS metadata when saving images on devices running
Android 10 and higher
.
This data is used only on the local device and WE DO NOT COLLECT this data for any other purposes.
com.google.android.gms.permission.AD_ID
This permission is required to access
Advertising ID
to serve ads.
For more information, see
Details of the third-party services we use > AdMob
.
RETENTION OF DATA
We will retain your data only for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. We will retain and use your data to the extent necessary to comply with our legal obligations (for example, if we are required to retain your data to comply with applicable laws), resolve disputes, and enforce our legal agreements and policies.
We will also retain Usage Data for internal analysis purposes. Usage Data is generally retained for a shorter period, except when this data is used to strengthen the security or to improve the functionality of our Service, or we are legally obligated to retain this data for longer time periods.
TRANSFER OF DATA
Your information may be transferred to – and maintained on – computers located outside of your state, province, country or other governmental jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ from those of your jurisdiction.
If you are located outside United States, please note that we transfer the data to United States and process it there.
If you are located inside the European Union, European Economic Area, the United Kingdom or Switzerland, please note that we transfer the data to outside of European Union, European Economic Area, United Kingdom or Switzerland and process it there.
We will take all the steps reasonably necessary to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy and no transfer of your data will take place to an organisation or a country unless there are adequate controls in place including the security of your data and other information.
DISCLOSURE OF DATA
We may disclose personal information that we collect, or you provide:
Disclosure for Law Enforcement.
Under certain circumstances, we may be required to disclose your data if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.
Business Transaction.
If we or our subsidiaries are involved in a merger, acquisition or asset sale, your data may be transferred.
Other cases. We may disclose your information also:
to our subsidiaries and affiliates;
to contractors, service providers, and other third parties we use to support our business;
to fulfill the purpose for which you provide it;
for any other purpose disclosed by us when you provide the information;
with your consent in any other cases;
if we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to protect the rights, property, or safety of the Company, our customers, or others.
SECURITY OF DATA
The security of your data is important to us but remember that no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your data, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
DATA DELETION REQUEST
Find this information in the
Data Deletion Request
documentation.
