CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
Our Services are not intended for use by children under the age of 13 (“
Child
” or “
Children
”).
We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from Children. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a Child without verification of parental consent where this is required, we will delete that information as quickly as possible. If you believe that we might have any information from or about a Child, please contact us using the contact information provided below.
CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY
We may, in its sole discretion, modify or update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date at the top of this Privacy Policy indicates when this Privacy Policy was last revised.
Any changes to the Privacy Policy will become effective when we post the revised Privacy Policy on this site (or as otherwise indicated at the time of posting).
Your use of our Service after those changes become effective means that you accept the revised Privacy Policy. It is your responsibility to review our Privacy Policy from time to time to ensure that you continue to agree with all of its terms.
CONTACT US
If you have questions or comments about this Privacy Policy, please feel free to
contact us
